Liu Zixu of Team China won the gold medal in the para biathlon men's sprint sitting at the National Biathlon Center in Zhangjiakou, north China's Hebei Province. Liu Sitong of Team China pocketed the bronze medal in the para alpine skiing women's downhill sitting at the National Alpine Skiing Center in Yanqing, Beijing. Henrieta Farkasova of Team Slovakia won the first gold medal at the 2022 Winter Paralympics in the para alpine skiing women's downhill vision impaired at the National Alpine Skiing Center in Yanqing, Beijing.